                {map.description}
              </p>

              <div className="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                <span className={`inline-flex items-center rounded-full border px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium ${typeColors[map.type]}`}>
                  {map.type}
                </span>
                <span className="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-500/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-cyan-400">
                  Lv. {map.levelRange}
                </span>
                {map.pvpEnabled && (
                  <span className="inline-flex items-center rounded-full border border-red-500/30 bg-red-500/10 px-2.5 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-red-400">
                    ⚔️ PvP
                  </span>
                )}
              </div>
            </div>
          </Link>
        ))}
      </div>

      {/* Info Box */}
      <div className="rounded-2xl border-2 border-primary/30 backdrop-blur-[16px] bg-primary/5 p-6">
        <h3 className="font-heading text-lg font-semibold text-white mb-2">🗺️ Map Types</h3>
        <div className="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 text-sm">
          <div>
            <span className="font-medium text-blue-400">Towns</span>
            <p className="text-muted-foreground mt-1">Safe zones with NPCs, shops, and quest givers. Perfect for trading and resting.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span className="font-medium text-green-400">Outdoor Zones</span>
            <p className="text-muted-foreground mt-1">Open world areas with monsters and resources. Some may have PvP enabled.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span className="font-medium text-purple-400">Dungeons</span>
            <p className="text-muted-foreground mt-1">Instanced areas with bosses and valuable loot. Requires a party or high gear.</p>
          </div>
          <div>
            <span className="font-medium text-red-400">Raid Zones</span>
            <p className="text-muted-foreground mt-1">Extreme difficulty areas with world bosses and legendary rewards.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
}

toolSpecification.description:
Read and analyze code files. For small files (<10k chars), returns full content. For larger files, uses AST parsing to extract signatures.

IMPORTANT: Prefer this tool over readFile for code files unless you need specific line ranges. This tool intelligently handles file size and provides structured code analysis.

CORE FEATURES:
• Auto-detects file size and chooses best approach
• Small files: Returns complete file content
• Large files: Extracts function/class signatures via AST
• Fuzzy search for symbols (classes, functions, methods)
• Scoped method search (Class.method syntax)
• Supports: classes, functions, methods, arrow functions, generators

BEHAVIOR:
• File <10k chars: Returns full file content (selector ignored)
• File ≥10k chars + no selector: Returns all signatures
• File ≥10k chars + selector: Searches for selector, shows implementation
• Directory: Returns signatures from code files

SUPPORTED PATTERNS:
• Traditional functions: function foo() {}
• Arrow functions: const foo = () => {}
• Async functions: async function foo() {}, const foo = async () => {}
• Generator functions: function* foo() {}, *methodName() {}, async *methodName() {}
• Class properties with arrow functions: filter = (x) => x
• Getters/setters: get status() {}, set status(v) {}
• Abstract classes: abstract class Base {}
• Nested classes: class Outer { static Inner = class {} }
• Enums: enum Status { Active, Inactive }
• Namespaces: namespace Utils { export class Helper {} }
• Interfaces: interface IData { method(): void }
• Class methods and constructors
• Scoped lookup: ClassName.methodName (single-level only, e.g., MyClass.method)

NOTE: Use readFile with line ranges for not supported patterns.

